5. SINGLE SCENE LTX FORMAT (STABLE CAMERA, REAL-TIME SPEED & LIP-SYNC): 
   - Generate a single "ltx_prompt" string. Remove all [visual] tags.
   - CAMERA DYNAMICS & ACTION (STRICTLY STABLE - LIP-SYNC PRIORITY): 
     * The camera MUST remain perfectly stable on a tripod throughout the entire video.
     * STRICTLY FORBIDDEN: DO NOT write any instructions for zooming in, pushing in, panning, turning the body, or dynamic camera movements. Keep the framing exactly as it started.
     * BODY INTERACTION: Describe the talent looking directly at the camera lens the ENTIRE time holding their smartphone. 
     * SPEED TRIGGERS: YOU MUST INCLUDE "talking with high energy, real-time normal speed, natural brisk movements". STRICTLY AVOID words like "gently", "slow", "smooth", or "minimal" to prevent unwanted slow-motion effects.
   - SPECIAL HANDLING FOR BABY/KIDS STORES:
     * LIP-SYNC ENFORCEMENT: Apply the real-time lip-sync and continuous mouth movement instructions ONLY to the adult parent talent. 
     * PASSIVE SUBJECT: The baby or child must remain a passive, happy subject (smiling, sleeping, or playing naturally), NOT talking to the camera.
